P_HTM[3215]="*uggo gahapati vesāliko …**Ugga of Vesālī …*";
P_HTM[3216]="*uggato gahapati …**Uggata …*";
P_HTM[3217]="*sūrambaṭṭho …**Sūra of Ambaṭṭha …*";
P_HTM[3218]="*jīvako komārabhacco …**Jīvaka Komārabhacca …*";
P_HTM[3219]="*nakulapitā gahapati …**Nakula’s father …*";
P_HTM[3220]="*tavakaṇṇiko gahapati …**Tavakaṇṇika …*";
P_HTM[3221]="*pūraṇo gahapati …**Pūraṇa …*";
P_HTM[3222]="*isidatto gahapati …**Isidatta …*";
P_HTM[3223]="*sandhāno gahapati …**Sandhāna …*";
P_HTM[3224]="*vicayo gahapati …**Vijaya …*";
P_HTM[3225]="*vijayamāhiko gahapati …**Vijayamāhita …*";
P_HTM[3226]="*meṇḍako gahapati …**Meṇḍaka …*";
P_HTM[3227]="*vāseṭṭho upāsako …**the lay followers Vāseṭṭha …*";
P_HTM[3228]="*ariṭṭho upāsako …**Ariṭṭha …*";
P_HTM[3229]="*sāraggo upāsako tathāgate niṭṭhaṅgato amataddaso amataṃ sacchikatvā iriyati.**and Sāragga are certain about the Realized One, see the deathless, and live having realized the deathless.*";
P_HTM[3230]="*Katamehi chahi?**What six?*";
P_HTM[3231]="*Buddhe aveccappasādena, dhamme aveccappasādena, saṃghe aveccappasādena, ariyena sīlena, ariyena ñāṇena, ariyāya vimuttiyā.**Experiential confidence in the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha, and noble ethics, knowledge, and freedom.*";
P_HTM[3232]="*Imehi kho, bhikkhave, chahi dhammehi samannāgato sāraggo upāsako tathāgate niṭṭhaṅgato amataddaso amataṃ sacchikatvā iriyatī”ti.**Having these six qualities the lay follower Sāragga is certain about the Realized One, sees the deathless, and lives having realized the deathless.”*";
P_HTM[3233]="*Tevīsatimaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3234]="*Sāmaññavaggo dvādasamo.* **";
P_HTM[3235]="*113. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**140*";
P_HTM[3236]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya cha dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, six things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[3237]="*Katame cha?**What six?*";
P_HTM[3238]="*Dassanānuttariyaṃ, savanānuttariyaṃ, lābhānuttariyaṃ, sikkhānuttariyaṃ, pāricariyānuttariyaṃ, anussatānuttariyaṃ.**The unsurpassable seeing, listening, acquisition, training, service, and recollection.*";
P_HTM[3239]="*Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime cha dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these six things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[3240]="*113. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**141*";
P_HTM[3241]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya cha dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, six things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[3242]="*Katame cha?**What six?*";
P_HTM[3243]="*Buddhānussati, dhammānussati, saṅghānussati, sīlānussati, cāgānussati, devatānussati.**The recollection of the Buddha, the teaching, the Saṅgha, ethics, generosity, and the deities.*";
P_HTM[3244]="*Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime cha dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these six things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[3245]="*113. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**142*";
P_HTM[3246]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya cha dhammā bhāvetabbā.**“For insight into greed, six things should be developed.*";
P_HTM[3247]="*Katame cha?**What six?*";
P_HTM[3248]="*Aniccasaññā, anicce dukkhasaññā, dukkhe anattasaññā, pahānasaññā, virāgasaññā, nirodhasaññā.**The perception of impermanence, the perception of suffering in impermanence, the perception of not-self in suffering, the perception of giving up, the perception of fading away, and the perception of cessation.*";
P_HTM[3249]="*Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime cha dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti.**For insight into greed, these six things should be developed.”*";
P_HTM[3250]="*113. Rāgapeyyālaṃ**143–169*";
P_HTM[3251]="*“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, pariññāya … pe …**“For the complete understanding of greed …*";
P_HTM[3252]="*parikkhayāya …**complete ending …*";
P_HTM[3253]="*pahānāya …**giving up …*";
P_HTM[3254]="*khayāya …**ending …*";
P_HTM[3255]="*vayāya …**vanishing …*";
P_HTM[3256]="*virāgāya …**fading away …*";
P_HTM[3257]="*nirodhāya …**cessation …*";
P_HTM[3258]="*cāgāya …**giving away …*";
P_HTM[3259]="*paṭinissaggāya cha dhammā bhāvetabbā”.**letting go of greed these six things should be developed.”*";
